  "details": "WordPress adivaha Travel Plugin 2.3 contains a time-based blind SQL injection vulnerability that allows unauthenticated attackers to manipulate database queries by injecting SQL code through the 'pid' GET parameter. Attackers can send requests to the /mobile-app/v3/ endpoint with crafted 'pid' values using XOR-based payloads to extract sensitive database information or cause denial of service.",
